+# Prior-Art And Anti-Repackaging Obstruction Is Already Active On The Stochastic Record
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` report constraint with `INFERRED` branch verdict
+
+Step-012 says the chain should stop before Step 2 if it cannot freeze one
+closest comparator and one concrete beyond-prior-art claim. On the current
+local record, that failure has already happened for the stochastic branch.
+
+The archive supports only a comparator neighborhood:
+`Constantin-Iyer` naming, generic circulation or back-to-label labels, and a
+known failure pattern of exact reformulation followed by expectation or
+localization nonclosure. It does not support one exact theorem-facing packet
+that says:
+
+- what gain is already standard;
+- what exact new gain this branch claims beyond that baseline;
+- and why that gain survives stopping, filtration, localization, and
+  import debt.
+
+So the honest filing is obstruction rather than survival:
+prior-art and anti-repackaging obstruction is already active on the stochastic
+record, and the branch should stop before further formal identity work.
+
+Filed from:
