+# Constantin-Iyer Is The Only Explicitly Named Stochastic Comparator Neighborhood On Disk
+
+Status: `VERIFIED`
+
+The local Step-012 record names `Constantin-Iyer` as the closest stochastic
+comparator neighborhood, but it never upgrades that name into a theorem-facing
+comparator packet.
+
+On disk, `Constantin-Iyer` appears only as one menu item beside
+`stochastic circulation identity` and `back-to-label observable`. The active
+chain and refined chain both demand one closest known stochastic
+representation and one exact gain beyond it, but neither source freezes a
+theorem statement, comparator memo, or exact already-standard vs new-gain
